ight I see a forge and anvil in my main pack....I cleared out the weapons and the anvil and forge were fully functional, only bad thing is they weighed over 400 stones and made it rather difficult to walk.  I tried to remove them from my pack with no success.  This bug is still around and I believe that is has to do with lag, i was stuck in my spot and had to page a GM to remove it from my pack, I asked the GM how it happened and he stated it was a mix of lag on the server and me doing alot at once.... You guys can try, i know it is till out there but am unable to get it to happen again....<P>------------------<BR>Look Out Behind You!!! NOOO!!!<P>* IN PORT YLEM *<BR>* AN EX POR *<BR>* VAS ORT FLAM *<BR>* CORP POR * * CORP POR *<P>Ashes to Ashes, Dust to Dust... If it wasn't for newbies, my spell book would rust.<P>DOH!</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">pagan DXM</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">oh well, guess ill throw it in the pile with the other rares  <IMG SRC="http://www.drtwister.com/ubb/NonCGI/frown.gif"><BR>BTW, the original bug had nothing to do w/ lag and doing alot of crap at once.  THere was just a simple trick to placing house addons into packs/pouches.  And that one has been fixed.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Hyman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The forge boats *are* still around.  I used to loot boats for a living, and last month I stumbled across a large boat with a forge a few spaces behind the mast.  <P>Unfortunately, the boat was empty besides that, and had no key aboard, so i couldn't check to see if it was collapsable.  My guess is that it wouldn't be, so those boats are bound to decay away over time....unless the bug to place the forges is still around.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">goo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdan